Hot soup, good soap. The fruits of our labour. The acrid air.

"Now faith is being sure of what we hope for and certain of what we do not see."

The narrator of this story is an idiot. He has lived all his adult life ignoring every sane advice. As a child he was obedient and generous. His days in school were full of accomplishment and glory. Then he was sent to college against his wishes. He didn't know what he wanted to be yet here he was in a strange town among strange folk, attending classes in subjects he did not like. So he became what he continues to be today - an idiot.

The reader is warned here that there is nothing useful in these ramblings. They are completely pointless. They have been printed here so that they may serve as a warning to those with ambitions and higher aspirations.
